nder Franco’s military dictatorship obsolete. This cultural history examines these modest but irreversible changes in the way people lived and thought about their lives during the last decade of the regime’s creed. Not a revolution necessarily, but transformational nevertheless, these changes in collective sensibility eased the political transition to democracy and the emergence of the eighties’ cultural movement la Movida.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aDrug abusexSocial aspectszSpainzMadridy20th century. 0aDrug abusezSpainzMadridxHistoryy20th century. 0aFashionxSocial aspectszSpainzMadridy20th century. 0aFashionzSpainzMadridxHistoryy20th century. 0aSexxSocial aspectszSpainzMadridy20th century. 0aSexzSpainzMadridxHistoryy20th century. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  a1970s.  aEurope.  aFranco.  aMadrid.  acultural studies.  ademocracy.  adictatorship.  adrugs.  afashion.  agender.  ahistory of Spain.  ala Movida.  amodernity.  arecreational drug use.  aseventies.  asex.  atransition.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751332040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487513320423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487513320.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  UTP Pilot eBook